com.energyxxer.commodore.types

Class TypeDictionary<T extends Type>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.energyxxer.commodore.types.TypeDictionary<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - Refers to the Type subclass which will be instantiated when a type is created in this dictionary and, by extension, the class of the object returned by methods create(java.lang.String) and get(java.lang.String).

    public class TypeDictionary<T extends Type>
extends java.lang.Object
    Class which contains all the types of a specific category in a certain namespace.
    See Also:
    Type, TypeManager, Namespace

        Parameters:
        namespace - The namespace all types created in this dictionary will belong to.
        category - The category all types created in this dictionary will belong to.

      • create

        public T create(java.lang.String name)
        Creates a type with the given name. If a type by that name already exists in this dictionary, that already-existing type will be returned. Otherwise it will be created.
        Parameters:
        name - The name the new type will be referred to as.
        Returns:
        The newly-created or already-existing type by the given name, of the type bound by T.
